        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 6 at 8:59AM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 858 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles south of Pine Hill, or 8 miles east of Thomasville, moving east
at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Camden, Yellow Bluff, Pine Hill, and Pine Apple.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 AM CDT for south central
and southwestern Alabama.</instruction>
